\title{Plurigrid: cognitive infrastructure for the next trillion minds}
\taxon{reference}
\author{monaduck1069}
\import{macros}
\date{2026-03-30}
\tag{plurigrid}
\tag{topos}
\tag{infrastructure}
\meta{external}{https://plurigrid.com}

\p{\strong{plurigrid.com} — the portal to autopoietic ergodicity and situated cognition. A research-grade substrate for decentralized computing, designed for extreme robustness and verifiable correctness across distributed systems, formal verification, and capability-based security.}

\subtree{\title{Problem}
\p{Information integration has exceeded human bandwidth. Systems demand real-time synthesis, yet context is fragmented across networks and applications. Whole-system approaches fail when critical causal dependencies lie outside their control.}
}

\subtree{\title{Solution: topos construction for social cognition}
\p{Universal topos construction for social cognition and interoperable meaning spaces. Intelligence amplification through compositional intent and decentralized coordination. Infrastructure and economic models for sense-making at scale.}
}

\subtree{\title{Origins}
\p{Started December 2022 focused on microgrid coordination and decentralized scientific expansion planning. IEEE1547 and IEEE2030 are underspecified; grids became causally open systems. Received a16z crypto accelerator funding ($500k, 7.5%). Coordination required modeling individual values, preferences, and information/resource flow.}
}

\subtree{\title{Architecture}
\p{Mathematical rigor with protocol-level invariants. VM operations become belief revision.}
\ol{
  \li{\strong{The Hard Substrate}: massively concurrent execution with non-blocking I/O, capability-based security with unforgeable references, resilient topology with proximity proofs.}
  \li{\strong{The Formal Laws}: state transitions as belief revision, invariants preventing arbitrary resource duplication, local-to-global consistency without central coordinators.}
  \li{\strong{The Translation Layer}: memory-safe zero-copy translation, pre-validation of inputs, high-performance routing for formal instructions and proofs.}
}
}

\subtree{\title{Capability network}
\p{\strong{zig-syrup} ([[bcf-0017]]): high-performance Zig implementation of OCapN Syrup with CapTP optimizations and Agent Client Protocol for capability-based networking. Includes computational topology and visualization primitives.}
\p{\strong{morph-prover-cli}: CLI environment for proof-oriented workflows and experimentation with verification tools.}
}

\subtree{\title{Research areas}
\ul{
  \li{\strong{Cognitive Continuity}: topOS as a co-generative layer adding social cognition to existing networks.}
  \li{\strong{Context-Specific Languages}: syntax-to-semantics affordances forming a topological space for joint modeling.}
  \li{\strong{Index of Good Vibes}: real-time information flow with fixed-point tracking and topological conjugacy classes.}
}
}

\subtree{\title{Time}
\p{Parallel systems cannot pretend time is sequential. The brain, Internet, and grid are parallel processing systems. Belief propagation and control flow follow continuous dynamics, not linear time. The trit-tick ([[bcf-0017]], [[bcf-0018]]) provides the temporal quantum compatible with this constraint.}
}

